      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REUBEN HILL (5) got around 460m in a strong 25.98 when winning a Grade 5 at Warragul last start. Can measure up again if runs up to latest time. PAW VADA (4) wasn't far away at the finish when 4th and beaten only 2.5 lengths (25.48) at this track. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to her name from six starts. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. KRAKEN TOMMY (1) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind Paw Hazelton (25.67) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Leading player again. SOLAR SPECTRUM (2) is worth including.",
